          <details class="document-details region-filters">
            <summary><span>realtime filters</span><span id="regionFilterSummary">off</span></summary>
            <div class="document-details-body">
              <div class="field" title="Image preprocessing applied in the OCR engine BEFORE detection (switches live, per frame). flatten = realtime upscale, illumination flattening, then unsharp. CLAHE-L = upscale and LAB L-channel CLAHE while preserving color. threshold = adaptive binarisation (Sauvola). isolate = keep text strokes, drop background. contrast = grayscale CLAHE. denoise = median. none = raw frame.">
                <label for="regionPreprocess">preprocess</label>
                <select id="regionPreprocess">
                  <option value="none">none</option>
                  <option value="flatten">flatten - illumination</option>
                  <option value="clahe-l">CLAHE-L</option>
                  <option value="threshold">threshold — adaptive binarise</option>
                  <option value="isolate">isolate — text only</option>
                  <option value="contrast">contrast — CLAHE</option>
                  <option value="denoise">denoise</option>
                </select>
              </div>
              <div class="field" title="One pattern per line. Each line is tried as a regular expression (case-insensitive) and falls back to literal text. Matching text is removed from OCR results before translation, so fixed watermarks and channel names stop polluting the translation cache.">
                <label for="regionDropPatterns">drop patterns (one per line)</label>
                <textarea id="regionDropPatterns" rows="3" spellcheck="false"></textarea>
              </div>
              <label class="field" style="flex-direction:row;align-items:center;gap:8px;cursor:pointer;" title="For moving / animated subtitles (lyric videos) over a busy background: re-detect the text box every frame so a moving line isn't clipped or missed, OCR without waiting for the scene to settle, and drop detected text not in the source language (background noise). Costs more CPU; works best with the capture box dragged large over the whole area the text roams, and a non-auto source language set.">
                <input id="regionMotionMode" type="checkbox">
                <span>motion subtitles (moving / complex background)</span>
              </label>
            </div>
          </details>
          <div id="regionStage" class="region-stage" tabindex="0">
            <video id="regionVideo" autoplay muted playsinline></video>
            <div id="regionPlaceholder" class="region-placeholder">Capture a screen or window, then drag a box over the dialogue area. Release to translate; drag inside to move, corners to resize, Esc to clear. Tip: choose the Window tab when you need capture to follow one app window.</div>
            <div id="regionSelection" class="region-selection hidden">
